HEADWORD: Whinberry
<hw>Whin"ber*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>The English bilberry; -- so called because it grows on moors among
the whins, or furze.</def> <rj><au>Dr. Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
